The paper deals with the existence and uniqueness conditions in Compressive Sensing (CS), which are fundamental concepts in Information Theory (cs.IT) and Signal Processing (cs.SP). The paper also focuses on the Coherence Index, which is a metric used to measure the sparsity of signals, making it relevant to Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Numerical Analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the paper discusses the practical implementation of CS systems, which falls under the category of Multimedia (cs.MM).
